Description.
Adult (
Figs. 53, 54
) wingspan 12.0̄ 
15.5 mm
. Forewing with two different patterns: one with several golden dots on costa, with dense golden spots below basal 2/3 of costa, dorsal fascia slightly narrowed anteriorly, reaching distal 2/3 of costa, distal 1/3 of wing suffused with golden dots, tornus with a golden dot extending to apex (
Fig. 53
); the other with ground color silvery grayish white, dorsal fascia from before middle of wing, wide on basal 1/3, narrower on distal 2/3, reaching before distal end of cell, tornus with a golden dot not extended (
Fig. 54
).
